{"parentUuid":"503e8994-5e32-41c1-ae70-21b6679013da","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"afd7b3466a6880b47","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01Y9J51QWN7J3mEC4NjCvRUv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01KG5UHbYtgy124zMjUYadAV","name":"WebSearch","input":{"query":"model collapse training on self-generated data failure mode"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1003,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5871,"cache_read_input_tokens":5811,"output_tokens":295,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5871},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1003,"output_tokens":295,"cache_read_input_tokens":5811,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5871,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5871,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"tools_changed","cache_missed_input_tokens":7725}}},"requestId":"req_011CcG22xRQyn4GsvyBAMjht","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","attributionSkill":"deep-research","type":"assistant","uuid":"59263626-0bb0-4ae1-b95e-672d01fa19ef","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:34.428Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"eeb90544-96eb-4097-9ee4-a20138530883","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"afd7b3466a6880b47","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Wj6a9753Cn8iHN53NVdwei","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Darwin Gödel Machine Sakana AI self-improving coding agent SWE-bench results\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Self-Improving AI: Darwin Gödel Machine Evolves Code\",\"url\":\"https://www.ikangai.com/self-improving-ai-darwin-godel-machine-evolves-code/\"},{\"title\":\"Darwin Gödel Machine: A Self-Improving AI Agent That Evolves Code Using Foundation Models and Real-World Benchmarks - MarkTechPost\",\"url\":\"https://www.marktechpost.com/2025/06/06/darwin-godel-machine-a-self-improving-ai-agent-that-evolves-code-using-foundation-models-and-real-world-benchmarks/\"},{\"title\":\"Sakana AI Unveils Darwin Gödel Machine: The Self-Improving AI Rewriting Its Own Code | StartupHub.ai\",\"url\":\"https://www.startuphub.ai/sakana-ai-unveils-darwin-godel-machine-the-self-improving-ai-rewriting-its-own-code/\"},{\"title\":\"Sakana AI's Darwin-Gödel Machine evolves by rewriting its own code to boost performance\",\"url\":\"https://the-decoder.com/sakana-ais-darwin-godel-machine-evolves-by-rewriting-its-own-code-to-boost-performance/\"},{\"title\":\"Sakana AI on X: \\\"Our experiments demonstrate that the Darwin Gödel Machine can continuously self-improve by modifying its own codebase. On SWE-bench, DGM automatically improved its performance from 20% to 50%. The figure here shows the performance progress over iterations, and also a summary of https://t.co/RjxapMTQN3\\\" / X\",\"url\":\"https://x.com/SakanaAILabs/status/1928447873362153669\"},{\"title\":\"Darwin Gödel Machine - by Grigory Sapunov - Gonzo ML\",\"url\":\"https://gonzoml.substack.com/p/darwin-godel-machine\"},{\"title\":\"The Darwin Gödel Machine: AI that improves itself by rewriting its own code\",\"url\":\"https://sakana.ai/dgm/\"},{\"title\":\"Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2505.22954\"},{\"title\":\"The Sequence Research #673: Infinite Self-Improvement: Unpacking Sakana's Darwin Gödel Machine\",\"url\":\"https://thesequence.substack.com/p/the-sequence-research-673-infinite\"},{\"title\":\"Darwin Gödel Machine: Self-Improving AI Agents - AI Papers Academy\",\"url\":\"https://aipapersacademy.com/darwin-godel-machine/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Darwin Gödel Machine from Sakana AI:\n\n## Overview\n\nResearchers from the University of British Columbia, Vector Institute, and Sakana AI developed the Darwin Gödel Machine (DGM), an AI system that can rewrite its own code to become a better programmer.\n\n## How It Works\n\nThe Darwin Gödel Machine is an AI agent designed to iteratively improve its own source code, leveraging foundational models to propose code improvements and integrating these changes into its own operating logic. The system evolves by continuously editing its own code, guided by performance metrics from real-world coding benchmarks such as SWE-bench and Polyglot.\n\n## SWE-Bench Results\n\nThe key results are impressive: Starting from a baseline performance of just 20%, the Darwin Gödel Machine autonomously improved itself to achieve 50% accuracy on SWE-bench, a challenging benchmark that tests AI's ability to solve real GitHub issues.\n\n## Additional Performance\n\nOn Polyglot, the DGM jumped performance from an initial 14.2% to 30.7%, which far surpasses the representative hand-designed agent by Aider.\n\n## Key Features\n\nNew agents are added to an ever-expanding archive of interesting agents, allowing future self-modifications to branch off from any agent in this growing archive for parallel exploration of many different evolutionary paths, which helps DGM discover truly novel solutions and avoid getting trapped in suboptimal designs.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"2c9b2414-1ce7-475b-b8d4-fe84b8eea982","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:41.237Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"Darwin Gödel Machine Sakana AI self-improving coding agent SWE-bench results","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_017VFy8KaegGHRJk6CrLk5gb","content":[{"title":"Self-Improving AI: Darwin Gödel Machine Evolves Code","url":"https://www.ikangai.com/self-improving-ai-darwin-godel-machine-evolves-code/"},{"title":"Darwin Gödel Machine: A Self-Improving AI Agent That Evolves Code Using Foundation Models and Real-World Benchmarks - MarkTechPost","url":"https://www.marktechpost.com/2025/06/06/darwin-godel-machine-a-self-improving-ai-agent-that-evolves-code-using-foundation-models-and-real-world-benchmarks/"},{"title":"Sakana AI Unveils Darwin Gödel Machine: The Self-Improving AI Rewriting Its Own Code | StartupHub.ai","url":"https://www.startuphub.ai/sakana-ai-unveils-darwin-godel-machine-the-self-improving-ai-rewriting-its-own-code/"},{"title":"Sakana AI's Darwin-Gödel Machine evolves by rewriting its own code to boost performance","url":"https://the-decoder.com/sakana-ais-darwin-godel-machine-evolves-by-rewriting-its-own-code-to-boost-performance/"},{"title":"Sakana AI on X: \"Our experiments demonstrate that the Darwin Gödel Machine can continuously self-improve by modifying its own codebase. On SWE-bench, DGM automatically improved its performance from 20% to 50%. The figure here shows the performance progress over iterations, and also a summary of https://t.co/RjxapMTQN3\" / X","url":"https://x.com/SakanaAILabs/status/1928447873362153669"},{"title":"Darwin Gödel Machine - by Grigory Sapunov - Gonzo ML","url":"https://gonzoml.substack.com/p/darwin-godel-machine"},{"title":"The Darwin Gödel Machine: AI that improves itself by rewriting its own code","url":"https://sakana.ai/dgm/"},{"title":"Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2505.22954"},{"title":"The Sequence Research #673: Infinite Self-Improvement: Unpacking Sakana's Darwin Gödel Machine","url":"https://thesequence.substack.com/p/the-sequence-research-673-infinite"},{"title":"Darwin Gödel Machine: Self-Improving AI Agents - AI Papers Academy","url":"https://aipapersacademy.com/darwin-godel-machine/"}]},"Based on the search results, here's what I found about Darwin Gödel Machine from Sakana AI:\n\n## Overview\n\nResearchers from the University of British Columbia, Vector Institute, and Sakana AI developed the Darwin Gödel Machine (DGM), an AI system that can rewrite its own code to become a better programmer.\n\n## How It Works\n\nThe Darwin Gödel Machine is an AI agent designed to iteratively improve its own source code, leveraging foundational models to propose code improvements and integrating these changes into its own operating logic. The system evolves by continuously editing its own code, guided by performance metrics from real-world coding benchmarks such as SWE-bench and Polyglot.\n\n## SWE-Bench Results\n\nThe key results are impressive: Starting from a baseline performance of just 20%, the Darwin Gödel Machine autonomously improved itself to achieve 50% accuracy on SWE-bench, a challenging benchmark that tests AI's ability to solve real GitHub issues.\n\n## Additional Performance\n\nOn Polyglot, the DGM jumped performance from an initial 14.2% to 30.7%, which far surpasses the representative hand-designed agent by Aider.\n\n## Key Features\n\nNew agents are added to an ever-expanding archive of interesting agents, allowing future self-modifications to branch off from any agent in this growing archive for parallel exploration of many different evolutionary paths, which helps DGM discover truly novel solutions and avoid getting trapped in suboptimal designs."],"durationSeconds":7.565558583000675,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"eeb90544-96eb-4097-9ee4-a20138530883","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"075b7818-532d-4428-a924-2f0c8e217184","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"afd7b3466a6880b47","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VZTiTNTDVHn99SbXw6fV28","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"STOP Self-Taught Optimizer recursive self-improvement language model paper\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"[2310.02304] Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2310.02304\"},{\"title\":\"Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation\",\"url\":\"http://opt-ml.org/papers/2023/paper21.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - microsoft/stop: Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/microsoft/stop\"},{\"title\":\"The Dawn of Recursive Intelligence: Microsoft’s Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP) Breaks New Ground | by Ahmed Ghazouani | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@nibniw/the-dawn-of-recursive-intelligence-microsofts-self-taught-optimizer-stop-breaks-new-ground-96a562c10de3\"},{\"title\":\"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2310.02304\"},{\"title\":\"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving ...\",\"url\":\"https://openreview.net/pdf?id=46Zgqo4QIU\"},{\"title\":\"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation | AI Research Paper Details\",\"url\":\"https://www.aimodels.fyi/papers/arxiv/self-taught-optimizer-stop-recursively-self-improving\"},{\"title\":\"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation - Microsoft Research\",\"url\":\"https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/publication/self-taught-optimizer-stop-recursively-self-improving-code-generation/\"},{\"title\":\"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation | OpenReview\",\"url\":\"https://openreview.net/forum?id=46Zgqo4QIU\"},{\"title\":\"[PDF] Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation | Semantic Scholar\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Self-Taught-Optimizer-(STOP):-Recursively-Code-Zelikman-Lorch/3fe940a1f121f083cb90c568fc6fa2951bb27dda\"}]\n\nI found comprehensive information about the STOP paper. Here's what the search revealed:\n\n## Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP) Paper Overview\n\nThe Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP) is a method in which code that applies a language model to improve arbitrary solutions is applied recursively to improve itself.\n\n**How It Works:**\n\nThe approach starts with a seed \"improver\" that improves an input program according to a given utility function by querying an LM several times and returning the best solution, then runs this seed improver to improve itself. Across a small set of downstream tasks, the resulting improved improver generates programs with significantly better performance than its seed improver.\n\n**Self-Improvement Strategies:**\n\nA variety of self-improvement strategies are proposed by the language model, including beam search, genetic algorithms, and simulated annealing.\n\n**Key Caveat:**\n\nSince the language models themselves are not altered, this is not full recursive self-improvement. Nonetheless, it demonstrates that a modern language model, GPT-4 in their experiments, is capable of writing code that can call itself to improve itself.\n\n**Publication Details:**\n\nThe paper was published on October 3, 2023, as a collaborative effort by researchers Eric Zelikman, Eliana Lorch, Lester Mackey, and Adam Tauman Kalai.\n\nThe paper is available on arXiv (2310.02304) and represents research from Microsoft and Stanford University.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"2681a5fd-f704-4bda-883c-ace7a3ca218e","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:42.383Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"STOP Self-Taught Optimizer recursive self-improvement language model paper","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01LfdLsLMiq6vLJL23EaZhGB","content":[{"title":"[2310.02304] Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2310.02304"},{"title":"Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation","url":"http://opt-ml.org/papers/2023/paper21.pdf"},{"title":"GitHub - microsoft/stop: Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/microsoft/stop"},{"title":"The Dawn of Recursive Intelligence: Microsoft’s Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP) Breaks New Ground | by Ahmed Ghazouani | Medium","url":"https://medium.com/@nibniw/the-dawn-of-recursive-intelligence-microsofts-self-taught-optimizer-stop-breaks-new-ground-96a562c10de3"},{"title":"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2310.02304"},{"title":"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving ...","url":"https://openreview.net/pdf?id=46Zgqo4QIU"},{"title":"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation | AI Research Paper Details","url":"https://www.aimodels.fyi/papers/arxiv/self-taught-optimizer-stop-recursively-self-improving"},{"title":"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation - Microsoft Research","url":"https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/publication/self-taught-optimizer-stop-recursively-self-improving-code-generation/"},{"title":"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation | OpenReview","url":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=46Zgqo4QIU"},{"title":"[PDF] Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation | Semantic Scholar","url":"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Self-Taught-Optimizer-(STOP):-Recursively-Code-Zelikman-Lorch/3fe940a1f121f083cb90c568fc6fa2951bb27dda"}]},"I found comprehensive information about the STOP paper. Here's what the search revealed:\n\n## Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP) Paper Overview\n\nThe Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP) is a method in which code that applies a language model to improve arbitrary solutions is applied recursively to improve itself.\n\n**How It Works:**\n\nThe approach starts with a seed \"improver\" that improves an input program according to a given utility function by querying an LM several times and returning the best solution, then runs this seed improver to improve itself. Across a small set of downstream tasks, the resulting improved improver generates programs with significantly better performance than its seed improver.\n\n**Self-Improvement Strategies:**\n\nA variety of self-improvement strategies are proposed by the language model, including beam search, genetic algorithms, and simulated annealing.\n\n**Key Caveat:**\n\nSince the language models themselves are not altered, this is not full recursive self-improvement. Nonetheless, it demonstrates that a modern language model, GPT-4 in their experiments, is capable of writing code that can call itself to improve itself.\n\n**Publication Details:**\n\nThe paper was published on October 3, 2023, as a collaborative effort by researchers Eric Zelikman, Eliana Lorch, Lester Mackey, and Adam Tauman Kalai.\n\nThe paper is available on arXiv (2310.02304) and represents research from Microsoft and Stanford University."],"durationSeconds":8.031251333000139,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"075b7818-532d-4428-a924-2f0c8e217184","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"503e8994-5e32-41c1-ae70-21b6679013da","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"afd7b3466a6880b47","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TAL1i2hgNLeQSsJUUyFoRZ","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"self-improving coding agent SICA benchmark success rate weak model bootstrap\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"GitHub - MaximeRobeyns/self_improving_coding_agent: A coding agent framework, that works on its own codebase. · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/MaximeRobeyns/self_improving_coding_agent\"},{\"title\":\"Self-Improving Coding Agent (SICA)\",\"url\":\"https://www.emergentmind.com/topics/self-improving-coding-agent-sica\"},{\"title\":\"[Literature Review] A Self-Improving Coding Agent\",\"url\":\"https://www.themoonlight.io/en/review/a-self-improving-coding-agent\"},{\"title\":\"A Self-Improving Coding Agent\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2504.15228v2\"},{\"title\":\"A Self-Improving Coding Agent Maxime Robeyns, University of Bristol\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2504.15228\"},{\"title\":\"Published as a workshop paper at ICLR 2025 SSI-FM A SELF-IMPROVING CODING AGENT\",\"url\":\"https://openreview.net/pdf?id=rShJCyLsOr\"},{\"title\":\"Huxley-Gödel Machine for Coding Agents\",\"url\":\"https://www.emergentmind.com/papers/2510.21614\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - hexo-ai/sia: SIA is a Self Improving AI framework to autonomously improve the performance of any AI system (Model / Agent) on a benchmark task. · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/hexo-ai/sia\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about self-improving coding agents (SICA) and related benchmarks:\n\n## SICA Overview and Performance\n\nA Self-Improving Coding Agent (SICA) is capable of editing its own codebase to improve itself with respect to its cost, speed and benchmark performance. Performance improves from 17% to 53% on a random subset of SWE-Bench Verified, even with consideration given to safety constraints and resource efficiency.\n\n## Weak Model Bootstrap and Challenges\n\nOne of the key challenges with SICA systems involves weak models. Weak models degrade self-improvement when tasked with frequent tool synthesis. Additionally, a stronger LLM can build a scaffold for a weaker LLM, and the weaker agent has the necessary building blocks to bootstrap these features and specialise itself to the distribution of benchmark tasks.\n\n## Benchmark Testing\n\nThe agent was tested on SWE Bench Verified, LiveCodeBench, and synthetic benchmarks, with results showing performance gains ranging from 17% to 53% on a random subset of SWE Bench Verified.\n\nThe research demonstrates that while SICA systems can achieve significant performance improvements through self-modification, the underlying capability of the base model remains a critical limiting factor.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"6b169d2d-b230-4962-9a7c-a373267b3137","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:42.527Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"self-improving coding agent SICA benchmark success rate weak model bootstrap","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01Ja5zWjpU3x2UA7xsdjhQw5","content":[{"title":"GitHub - MaximeRobeyns/self_improving_coding_agent: A coding agent framework, that works on its own codebase. · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/MaximeRobeyns/self_improving_coding_agent"},{"title":"Self-Improving Coding Agent (SICA)","url":"https://www.emergentmind.com/topics/self-improving-coding-agent-sica"},{"title":"[Literature Review] A Self-Improving Coding Agent","url":"https://www.themoonlight.io/en/review/a-self-improving-coding-agent"},{"title":"A Self-Improving Coding Agent","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2504.15228v2"},{"title":"A Self-Improving Coding Agent Maxime Robeyns, University of Bristol","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2504.15228"},{"title":"Published as a workshop paper at ICLR 2025 SSI-FM A SELF-IMPROVING CODING AGENT","url":"https://openreview.net/pdf?id=rShJCyLsOr"},{"title":"Huxley-Gödel Machine for Coding Agents","url":"https://www.emergentmind.com/papers/2510.21614"},{"title":"GitHub - hexo-ai/sia: SIA is a Self Improving AI framework to autonomously improve the performance of any AI system (Model / Agent) on a benchmark task. · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/hexo-ai/sia"}]},"Based on the search results, here's what I found about self-improving coding agents (SICA) and related benchmarks:\n\n## SICA Overview and Performance\n\nA Self-Improving Coding Agent (SICA) is capable of editing its own codebase to improve itself with respect to its cost, speed and benchmark performance. Performance improves from 17% to 53% on a random subset of SWE-Bench Verified, even with consideration given to safety constraints and resource efficiency.\n\n## Weak Model Bootstrap and Challenges\n\nOne of the key challenges with SICA systems involves weak models. Weak models degrade self-improvement when tasked with frequent tool synthesis. Additionally, a stronger LLM can build a scaffold for a weaker LLM, and the weaker agent has the necessary building blocks to bootstrap these features and specialise itself to the distribution of benchmark tasks.\n\n## Benchmark Testing\n\nThe agent was tested on SWE Bench Verified, LiveCodeBench, and synthetic benchmarks, with results showing performance gains ranging from 17% to 53% on a random subset of SWE Bench Verified.\n\nThe research demonstrates that while SICA systems can achieve significant performance improvements through self-modification, the underlying capability of the base model remains a critical limiting factor."],"durationSeconds":7.903117999998853,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"503e8994-5e32-41c1-ae70-21b6679013da","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"59263626-0bb0-4ae1-b95e-672d01fa19ef","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"afd7b3466a6880b47","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KG5UHbYtgy124zMjUYadAV","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"model collapse training on self-generated data failure mode\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Model Collapse Risks in AI Training Data 2025 | Prevention Guide\",\"url\":\"https://www.influencers-time.com/mitigating-model-collapse-risks-in-ai-data-training-2025/\"},{\"title\":\"The AI Model Collapse Risk is Not Solved in 2025\",\"url\":\"https://www.winssolutions.org/ai-model-collapse-2025-recursive-training/\"},{\"title\":\"Why Self-Training Helps and Hurts: Denoising vs. Signal Forgetting\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2602.14029\"},{\"title\":\"AI model collapse: The synthetic data trap and how to avoid it\",\"url\":\"https://insights.manageengine.com/artificial-intelligence/ai-model-collapse-synthetic-data-trap/\"},{\"title\":\"What Is Model Collapse? Causes, Examples, and Fixes | Vegavid\",\"url\":\"https://vegavid.com/blog/what-is-model-collapse\"},{\"title\":\"Context Collapse: In-Context Learning and Model Collapse\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.00923\"},{\"title\":\"Model collapse explained: How synthetic training data breaks AI\",\"url\":\"https://www.techtarget.com/whatis/feature/Model-collapse-explained-How-synthetic-training-data-breaks-AI\"},{\"title\":\"ForTIFAI: Fending Off Recursive Training Induced Failure for AI Model Collapse\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2509.08972\"},{\"title\":\"A Closer Look at Model Collapse: From a Generalization-to-Memorization Perspective\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2509.16499v2\"},{\"title\":\"Strong Model Collapse\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2410.04840\"}]\n\nI found comprehensive information about model collapse from training on self-generated data. Here's what the research shows:\n\n## Definition and Core Mechanism\n\nModel collapse describes a progressive failure mode where models trained on data that includes outputs from other models (or their own earlier outputs) begin to lose information, diversity, and fidelity to real-world distributions. The core mechanism is a synthetic data feedback loop: model outputs get mixed into training data, then the next model learns from that mixture, and so on. Each cycle can amplify biases, remove rare events, and reduce entropy in the dataset.\n\n## Manifestation of Collapse\n\nOver successive generations, the system's view of reality narrows: rare details vanish, outputs become repetitive and unoriginal, and the model loses the variability that makes human‑generated content rich. The failure occurs in stages: In early model collapse, the model begins to lose information about probability tails. In late model collapse, the model blends together what should be distinct patterns in the data. Eventually, the outputs become increasingly similar to each other with little resemblance to the original data.\n\n## Research Evidence\n\nResearch teams fine-tuned Meta's OPT-125M on WikiText-2 and then trained successive \"generations\" on data written by the previous generation. Baseline performance after fine-tuning on real data reached 34 mean perplexity, but when later generations trained only on model-generated data, perplexity increased by ~20–28 points.\n\n## Mitigation Strategies\n\nMitigating this requires rigorous data provenance tracking, strict caps on the proportion of model-generated data (typically below 30-40%), continuous de-duplication, active human curation to refresh training data with ground truth, and adversarial detectors to identify and filter self-generated artifacts.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"5b6d537e-9470-4c85-92d0-b866e2f51efc","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:44.721Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"model collapse training on self-generated data failure mode","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_011CYUEzRq4733gRhTwRgTrf","content":[{"title":"Model Collapse Risks in AI Training Data 2025 | Prevention Guide","url":"https://www.influencers-time.com/mitigating-model-collapse-risks-in-ai-data-training-2025/"},{"title":"The AI Model Collapse Risk is Not Solved in 2025","url":"https://www.winssolutions.org/ai-model-collapse-2025-recursive-training/"},{"title":"Why Self-Training Helps and Hurts: Denoising vs. Signal Forgetting","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2602.14029"},{"title":"AI model collapse: The synthetic data trap and how to avoid it","url":"https://insights.manageengine.com/artificial-intelligence/ai-model-collapse-synthetic-data-trap/"},{"title":"What Is Model Collapse? Causes, Examples, and Fixes | Vegavid","url":"https://vegavid.com/blog/what-is-model-collapse"},{"title":"Context Collapse: In-Context Learning and Model Collapse","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.00923"},{"title":"Model collapse explained: How synthetic training data breaks AI","url":"https://www.techtarget.com/whatis/feature/Model-collapse-explained-How-synthetic-training-data-breaks-AI"},{"title":"ForTIFAI: Fending Off Recursive Training Induced Failure for AI Model Collapse","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2509.08972"},{"title":"A Closer Look at Model Collapse: From a Generalization-to-Memorization Perspective","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2509.16499v2"},{"title":"Strong Model Collapse","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2410.04840"}]},"I found comprehensive information about model collapse from training on self-generated data. Here's what the research shows:\n\n## Definition and Core Mechanism\n\nModel collapse describes a progressive failure mode where models trained on data that includes outputs from other models (or their own earlier outputs) begin to lose information, diversity, and fidelity to real-world distributions. The core mechanism is a synthetic data feedback loop: model outputs get mixed into training data, then the next model learns from that mixture, and so on. Each cycle can amplify biases, remove rare events, and reduce entropy in the dataset.\n\n## Manifestation of Collapse\n\nOver successive generations, the system's view of reality narrows: rare details vanish, outputs become repetitive and unoriginal, and the model loses the variability that makes human‑generated content rich. The failure occurs in stages: In early model collapse, the model begins to lose information about probability tails. In late model collapse, the model blends together what should be distinct patterns in the data. Eventually, the outputs become increasingly similar to each other with little resemblance to the original data.\n\n## Research Evidence\n\nResearch teams fine-tuned Meta's OPT-125M on WikiText-2 and then trained successive \"generations\" on data written by the previous generation. Baseline performance after fine-tuning on real data reached 34 mean perplexity, but when later generations trained only on model-generated data, perplexity increased by ~20–28 points.\n\n## Mitigation Strategies\n\nMitigating this requires rigorous data provenance tracking, strict caps on the proportion of model-generated data (typically below 30-40%), continuous de-duplication, active human curation to refresh training data with ground truth, and adversarial detectors to identify and filter self-generated artifacts."],"durationSeconds":10.051407499998808,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"59263626-0bb0-4ae1-b95e-672d01fa19ef","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
